-- Copper in London Declines by 0.5% to $6,574, Falling For First Day in Four
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-07T00:04:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/copper-in-london-declines-by-0-5-to-6-574-falling-for-first-day-in-four.html

          
          
             Copper in London declined by 0.5
percent to $6,574 a metric ton today. Aluminum dropped 0.9
percent to $1,978 a ton.  
          
          


  


        